quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  39,32,"So who is more unjust than one who fabricates a lie against Allah, and denies the truth when it comes to him? Is not the destination of disbelievers in hell?"
  39,33,"And those who brought this truth and those who testify for it – these are the pious."
  39,34,"For them is whatever they wish, before their Lord; this is the reward of the virtuous."
  39,35,"So that Allah may relieve them of their worst deeds, and reward them for the best deeds they had done."
  39,36,"Is not Allah Sufficient for His slave? And they threaten you with others beside Him! And whomever Allah sends astray – there is no guide for him."
  39,37,"And no one can mislead whomever Allah guides; is not Allah the Most Honourable, the Avenger?"
  39,38,"And if you ask them, “Who has created the heavens and the earth?”, they will surely say, “Allah”; say, “What is your opinion regarding those whom you worship other than Allah – if Allah wills to cause me some hardship, so will they avert the hardship sent by Him? Or if He wills to have mercy upon me, so will they restrain His mercy?” Proclaim, “Allah is Sufficient for me; the people who trust must rely only upon Him.”"
  39,39,"Proclaim, “O my people! Keep on with your works in your positions, I am doing mine; so you will soon come to know.” –"
  39,40,"“To whom will come a punishment that will disgrace, and upon whom descends the punishment that never ends.”"
